## 🚫 Custom Project Rules

### Enforce Project Patterns
```javascript
// Custom rules for your project patterns
const customRules = {
  // Enforce error handling patterns
  'custom/catch-error-handling': {
    create(context) {
      return {
        CatchClause(node) {
          if (!node.param) {
            context.report({
              node,
              message: 'Catch blocks must handle the error parameter',
            });
          }
        }
      };
    }
  },

  // Enforce async/await over promises
  'custom/prefer-async-await': {
    create(context) {
      return {
        CallExpression(node) {
          if (node.callee.property?.name === 'then') {
            context.report({
              node,
              message: 'Prefer async/await over .then() chains',
              fix(fixer) {
                // Auto-fix logic here
              }
            });
          }
        }
      };
    }
  },

  // Enforce proper logging
  'custom/structured-logging': {
    create(context) {
      return {
        CallExpression(node) {
          if (node.callee.object?.name === 'console') {
            context.report({
              node,
              message: 'Use structured logger instead of console',
              fix(fixer) {
                return fixer.replaceText(node.callee.object, 'logger');
              }
            });
          }
        }
      };
    }
  },
};
```

## 🔧 Auto-Fix Configuration

### Fixable Rules Setup
```json
// package.json scripts
{
  "scripts": {
    "lint": "eslint . --ext .ts,.tsx,.js,.jsx",
    "lint:fix": "eslint . --ext .ts,.tsx,.js,.jsx --fix",
    "lint:fix-dry": "eslint . --ext .ts,.tsx,.js,.jsx --fix-dry-run",
    "lint:changed": "eslint $(git diff --name-only HEAD | grep -E '\\.(ts|tsx|js|jsx)$')",
    "lint:staged": "lint-staged"
  }
}
```

